def "tale:china_carve_boat" "A man crossing a river drops his sword overboard, and calmly cuts a notch on the moving boat to mark the spot where it fell. When the boat docks, he dives in beneath the notch and is baffled to find nothing. Moral: he who ignores that the world has moved on will search in vain. — Lüshi Chunqiu"
