def "tale:china_cook_ding" "Cook Ding carves an ox for his lord with such ease that his blade glides through the joints and hollows untouched and stays keen for years, for he follows the natural lines and never forces the knife through bone. Moral: true mastery works with the grain of things, not against it. — Zhuangzi"
