def "tale:china_cover_ears" "A thief, trying to carry off a great bell too heavy to move, smashes it to pieces; when the blows ring out, he claps his hands over his own ears, reasoning that if he cannot hear the noise, no one else can. Moral: to deny a thing by shutting your own eyes to it deceives no one but yourself. — Lüshi Chunqiu"
