def "tale:china_frog_well" "A frog living at the bottom of a well boasts of his whole bright world, until a turtle from the Eastern Sea tells of an ocean no flood can fill and no drought can drain; the frog is struck dumb. Moral: one who knows only his own small world cannot judge the great. — Zhuangzi"
