def "tale:china_handan_walk" "A young man of Yan, admiring the elegant gait of the people of Handan, travels there to learn it; but he never masters their walk, and forgets his own, so that he must crawl home on hands and knees. Moral: in slavishly aping others you may lose what was already yours. — Zhuangzi"
