def "tale:china_mantis_chariot" "A praying mantis, in its fury, raises its forelegs to halt the wheels of an oncoming chariot, certain of its strength, and is crushed. Moral: to pit one's small force against the overwhelming is to perish for nothing. — Zhuangzi"
