def "tale:china_self_contradiction" "A man hawking weapons cries that his spear can pierce any shield, and that his shield can stop any spear. A bystander asks what happens when that spear strikes that shield, and the seller has no answer. Moral: two boasts that destroy each other cannot both be true. — Han Feizi"
