def "tale:china_snake_feet" "In a contest to draw a snake fastest for a prize of wine, the quickest finisher, with time to spare, adds feet to his snake to show off — and loses, for the judge rules that snakes have no feet, and the drawing is no longer a snake. Moral: needless embellishment spoils what was already complete. — Zhanguo Ce"
