def "tale:china_snipe_clam" "A clam opens on the bank and a snipe stabs at its flesh; the clam clamps the snipe's beak, and neither will let go. While they are locked in stalemate, a passing fisherman scoops up the pair. Moral: while two cling to their quarrel, a third carries off the prize. — Zhanguo Ce"
