def "tale:china_three_four" "A keeper of monkeys, short of food, tells them they will have three chestnuts each morning and four each evening; the monkeys rage. He then says four in the morning and three at night, and the monkeys are delighted — though the total is unchanged. Moral: the foolish are swayed by the framing, not the sum. — Zhuangzi"
