def "tale:china_yugong_mountain" "Old Yu Gong, blocked by two great mountains, sets his family to digging them away basketful by basketful, vowing that though he die, his sons and grandsons will carry on until it is done. Moved by such resolve, the gods themselves remove the peaks. Moral: unwavering effort across generations levels what seems immovable. — Liezi"
