def "tale:panchatantra_mouse_maiden" "A sage transforms a baby mouse into a girl and raises her; when she comes of age he seeks the mightiest husband in the world. The Sun yields to the Cloud that veils him, the Cloud to the Wind, the Wind to the Mountain that stops it, the Mountain to the Mice that burrow through it — so the girl is given to a mouse, and gladly becomes a mouse again. Moral: each is happiest returned to its own nature. — Panchatantra (attrib. Vishnu Sharma)"
ln tale:panchatantra_mouse_maiden fable sys:is_a
ln tale:panchatantra_mouse_maiden nature @illustrates
ln tale:panchatantra_mouse_maiden humility @illustrates
ln tale:panchatantra_mouse_maiden tale:japan_nezumi_yomeiri @parallels
set.add name="ontology.panchatantra_fables" id="tale:panchatantra_mouse_maiden"

def "tale:panchatantra_singing_donkey" "A donkey raiding a cucumber field by night grows so happy that it wishes to sing, and brays despite its jackal friend's warning that the noise will bring the guards. It sings; the watchmen come and beat it well. Moral: there is a time to be silent, and the fool who must perform finds it too late. — Panchatantra (attrib. Vishnu Sharma)"
ln tale:panchatantra_singing_donkey fable sys:is_a
ln tale:panchatantra_singing_donkey restraint @illustrates
ln tale:panchatantra_singing_donkey folly @illustrates
